    "source": "statement_20140917.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2014-09-17",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "74785c9e-1b1f-479a-9891-13579e6a3e38",
    "sentence": "The Committee seeks to achieve maximum employment and inflation at the rate of 2 percent over the longer run. In support of these goals, the Committee decided to keep the target range for the federal funds rate at 0 to 1/4 percent.",
    "source": "statement_20220126.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2022-01-26",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "01f8fd23-a2a2-4df8-8e83-eebff1846b0c",
    "sentence": "The Committee will continue to monitor the implications of incoming information for the economic outlook, including information related to public health, as well as global developments and muted inflation pressures, and will use its tools and act as appropriate to support the economy.",
    "source": "statement_20200729.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2020-07-29",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5a23dcbd-e375-4b25-8798-36ccd5ec02a1",
    "sentence": "The Committee is maintaining its existing policy of reinvesting principal payments from its holdings of agency debt and agency mortgage-backed securities in agency mortgage-backed securities and of rolling over maturing Treasury securities at auction.",
    "source": "statement_20170614.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2017-06-14",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5bc3e140-af34-41fd-986f-5b54dccde18d",
    "sentence": "To support a stronger economic recovery and to help ensure that inflation, over time, is at the rate most consistent with its dual mandate, the Committee will continue purchasing additional agency mortgage-backed securities at a pace of $40 billion per month.",
    "source": "statement_20121212.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2012-12-12",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "9de83f77-f9ef-4efb-8c3e-a58e0eb58f5b",
    "sentence": "Risks to the economic outlook remain, including from new variants of the virus.",
    "source": "statement_20220126.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2022-01-26",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "eb265683-1c0c-4c07-a75d-4dac3b4043ec",
    "sentence": "In addition, the Federal Reserve will buy up to $300 billion of Treasury securities by autumn.",
    "source": "statement_20090429.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2009-04-29",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "600d8df7-a162-40a2-934b-e2610d7234cc",
    "sentence": "These arrangements will now provide dollars in amounts of up to $30 billion and $6 billion to the ECB and the SNB, respectively, representing increases of $10 billion and $2 billion.",
    "source": "statement_20080311.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2008-03-11",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d897a55f-6426-46d1-82b0-e121e53bbbac",
    "sentence": "The Committee will closely monitor incoming information on economic and financial developments in coming months.",
    "source": "statement_20130731.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2013-07-31",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5c16f8c7-a3e0-49c5-beca-8f921d7a0b07",
    "sentence": "In view of realized and expected labor market conditions and inflation, the Committee decided to raise the target range for the federal funds rate to 3/4 to 1 percent.",
    "source": "statement_20170315.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2017-03-15",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b1c7fd76-cc39-4feb-aac8-229a42ed4dcb",
    "sentence": "The Committee will continue to carefully monitor the size and composition of the Federal Reserve's balance sheet in light of financial and economic developments.",
    "source": "statement_20090429.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2009-04-29",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "21cbc231-2fe2-4949-a6b6-d85ac821501d",
    "sentence": "In determining the timing and size of future adjustments to the stance of monetary policy, the Committee will assess realized and expected economic conditions relative to its maximum employment objective and its symmetric 2 percent inflation objective. This assessment will take into account a wide range of information, including measures of labor market conditions, indicators of inflation pressures and inflation expectations, and readings on financial and international developments.",
    "source": "statement_20200729.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2020-07-29",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "fdf30e4b-f416-463b-8f35-581a54d10809",
    "sentence": "In this context, the Committee judges that some inflation risks remain, and it will continue to monitor inflation developments carefully.",
    "source": "statement_20071211.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2007-12-11",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a0312442-1fec-4499-9ed4-1c9e263743dc",
    "sentence": "Beginning later this month, the Committee will increase its holdings of Treasury securities by at least $70 billion per month and of agency mortgageâbacked securities by at least $35 billion per month.",
    "source": "statement_20211103.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2021-11-03",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "84f9bbdd-1c6b-46da-bebf-050d0a7cf107",
    "sentence": "Recent developments, including the deterioration in financial market conditions, have increased the uncertainty surrounding the outlook for economic growth and inflation.",
    "source": "statement_20071211.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2007-12-11",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a47cb832-40dd-450b-9d21-610c85b45ea1",
    "sentence": "These facilities are designed to help improve liquidity conditions in U.S. dollar funding markets and to prevent the spread of strains to other markets and financial centers.",
    "source": "statement_20100509.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2010-05-09",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "affb8193-44f2-423b-8d47-3e9f81406b40",
    "sentence": "The Committee is maintaining its existing policy of reinvesting principal payments from its holdings of agency debt and agency mortgage-backed securities in agency mortgage-backed securities and of rolling over maturing Treasury securities at auction. Taken together, these actions should maintain downward pressure on longer-term interest rates, support mortgage markets, and help to make broader financial conditions more accommodative, which in turn should promote a stronger economic recovery and help to ensure that inflation, over time, is at the rate most consistent with the Committee's dual mandate.",
    "source": "statement_20131030.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2013-10-30",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "1e20905f-3df2-431d-b60f-86fdfc89b3e2",
    "sentence": "The extent and timing of any additional firming that may be needed to address these risks will depend on the evolution of the outlook for both inflation and economic growth, as implied by incoming information.",
    "source": "statement_20070131.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2007-01-31",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f7ced697-d221-48f5-8e61-33ed032e5455",
    "sentence": "However, downside risks to growth remain.",
    "source": "statement_20080318.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2008-03-18",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "25cd736f-1d3c-4e0e-a88c-7ab5e0273068",
    "sentence": "The Committee expects that economic conditions will evolve in a manner that will warrant only gradual increases in the federal funds rate; the federal funds rate is likely to remain, for some time, below levels that are expected to prevail in the longer run.",
    "source": "statement_20170201.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2017-02-01",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a9d2ad83-02f7-457b-822b-b52fa42079da",
    "sentence": "Market-based measures of inflation compensation remain low; survey-based measures of longer-term inflation expectations are little changed, on balance, in recent months.",
    "source": "statement_20160316.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2016-03-16",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6e7e6d9a-f78e-4dd7-8bc1-ea4bcfe4844c",
    "sentence": "The downside risks to growth and the upside risks to inflation are both of significant concern to the Committee.",
    "source": "statement_20080916.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2008-09-16",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6b140f39-b2ef-497b-81dd-b4864b8cc4b1",
    "sentence": "The effects of the coronavirus will weigh on economic activity in the near term and pose risks to the economic outlook. In light of these developments, the Committee decided to lower the target range for the federal funds rate to 0 to 1/4 percent.",
    "source": "statement_20200315.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2020-03-15",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "65a49be2-3d3b-46e5-82b1-1d4ec05e71eb",
    "sentence": "In support of its goals and in light of the shift in the balance of risks, the Committee decided to lower the target range for the federal funds rate by 1/4 percentage point to 3-1/2 to 3â3/4 percent.",
    "source": "statement_20251210.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2025-12-10",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "723f1b21-9420-4b31-b68b-75d8fdb7abae",
    "sentence": "In a related set of actions to support the credit needs of households and businesses, the Federal Reserve announced measures related to the discount window, intraday credit, bank capital and liquidity buffers, reserve requirements, andâin coordination with other central banksâthe U.S. dollar liquidity swap line arrangements.",
    "source": "statement_20200315.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2020-03-15",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "fb193083-e3c7-4c99-8892-f8255d52f29a",
    "sentence": "The stance of monetary policy remains accommodative, thereby supporting further improvement in labor market conditions and a return to 2 percent inflation.",
    "source": "statement_20161102.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2016-11-02",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e457078b-c3ed-4023-bc95-08f4cb19e876",
    "sentence": "The Committee will continue to evaluate its purchases of securities in light of the evolving economic outlook and conditions in financial markets.",
    "source": "statement_20100127.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2010-01-27",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e12ba299-74c7-4a3f-90c7-e28d44a0f5a7",
    "sentence": "The Committee's assessments will take into account a wide range of information, including readings on public health, labor market conditions, inflation pressures and inflation expectations, and financial and international developments.",
    "source": "statement_20221214.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2022-12-14",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6437345a-a389-4c74-a744-315b2352ace8",
    "sentence": "To that end, today the Bank of Canada, the Bank of England, the European Central Bank, the Federal Reserve, and the Swiss National Bank are announcing specific measures.",
    "source": "statement_20080311.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2008-03-11",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5a701382-b887-4290-b62b-80cf30d44012",
    "sentence": "The Committee continues to see the risks to the outlook for economic activity and the labor market as nearly balanced but is monitoring global economic and financial developments.",
    "source": "statement_20151028.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2015-10-28",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b0debb25-86d4-4a46-b5cc-a11b77a7aae2",
    "sentence": "The Committee will continue its purchases of Treasury and agency mortgage-backed securities, and employ its other policy tools as appropriate, until the outlook for the labor market has improved substantially in a context of price stability.",
    "source": "statement_20130731.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2013-07-31",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4c272506-b838-479c-b4a8-f8ccfd224215",
    "sentence": "The Committee is attentive to the risks to both sides of its dual mandate and judges that downside risks to employment have risen.",
    "source": "statement_20250917.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2025-09-17",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b7776e14-3cff-48b2-8cf0-8b26bc6b3dfd",
    "sentence": "Financial markets remain under considerable stress, and the tightening of credit conditions and the deepening of the housing contraction are likely to weigh on economic growth over the next few quarters.",
    "source": "statement_20080318.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2008-03-18",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f6a31c06-651a-4359-873e-eb156e197ceb",
    "sentence": "The Committee also decided to continue through the end of the year its program to extend the average maturity of its holdings of securities as announced in June, and it is maintaining its existing policy of reinvesting principal payments from its holdings of agency debt and agency mortgage-backed securities in agency mortgage-backed securities.",
    "source": "statement_20120801.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2012-08-01",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "58ee31bf-e578-46ed-ad0c-ef11d02ec534",
    "sentence": "The Federal Reserve is in the process of winding down its Term Auction Facility: $50 billion in 28-day credit will be offered on February 8 and $25 billion in 28-day credit will be offered at the final auction on March 8.",
    "source": "statement_20100127.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2010-01-27",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "cb9a8b51-0548-4c9f-92f7-e56f875730dc",
    "sentence": "In addition, the Federal Reserve will continue to increase its holdings of Treasury securities by at least $80 billion per month and of agency mortgageâbacked securities by at least $40 billion per month until substantial further progress has been made toward the Committee's maximum employment and price stability goals.",
    "source": "statement_20210616.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2021-06-16",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "98ebfe74-c544-4a09-b251-f203ef6f13f9",
    "sentence": "If the outlook for the labor market does not improve substantially, the Committee will continue its purchases of agency mortgage-backed securities, undertake additional asset purchases, and employ its other policy tools as appropriate until such improvement is achieved in a context of price stability.",
    "source": "statement_20121024.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2012-10-24",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "aece3c5f-d847-4162-92eb-1862809033a9",
    "sentence": "The Committee will regularly review the size and composition of its securities holdings and is prepared to adjust those holdings as appropriate.",
    "source": "statement_20111213.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2011-12-13",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "fb70809a-41e1-4e4f-b1e7-e65f1eab2a7f",
    "sentence": "The Committee is closely monitoring global economic and financial developments and is assessing their implications for the labor market and inflation, and for the balance of risks to the outlook.",
    "source": "statement_20160127.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2016-01-27",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "bd0a56f6-3213-4d7a-9491-996781517024",
    "sentence": "Since the coordinated actions taken in December 2007, the G-10 central banks have continued to work together closely and to consult regularly on liquidity pressures in funding markets.",
    "source": "statement_20080311.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2008-03-11",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8a8a55e7-805f-499c-b4df-76ea77772e13",
    "sentence": "It will be necessary to continue to monitor inflation developments carefully.",
    "source": "statement_20080430.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2008-04-30",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5fa31483-d48c-49e6-89c3-e286648b782f",
    "sentence": "The Committee is prepared to increase or reduce the pace of its purchases to maintain appropriate policy accommodation as the outlook for the labor market or inflation changes. In determining the size, pace, and composition of its asset purchases, the Committee will continue to take appropriate account of the likely efficacy and costs of such purchases as well as the extent of progress toward its economic objectives.",
    "source": "statement_20130731.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2013-07-31",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a82e4974-64d9-4547-a4fb-66bcd530cb6e",
    "sentence": "The Committee decided to keep the target range for the federal funds rate at 0 to 1/4 percent and expects it will be appropriate to maintain this target range until labor market conditions have reached levels consistent with the Committee's assessments of maximum employment and inflation has risen to 2 percent and is on track to moderately exceed 2 percent for some time.",
    "source": "statement_20211103.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2021-11-03",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "597c771f-ce4d-4e49-ab14-e272302301e2",
    "sentence": "To support the flow of credit to households and businesses, over coming months the Federal Reserve will increase its holdings of Treasury securities and agency residential and commercial mortgage-backed securities at least at the current pace to sustain smooth market functioning, thereby fostering effective transmission of monetary policy to broader financial conditions.",
    "source": "statement_20200729.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2020-07-29",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b11f2609-4f53-4efd-af89-5b1c44d1149b",
    "sentence": "The Committee will carefully monitor actual and expected inflation developments relative to its symmetric inflation goal.",
    "source": "statement_20180502.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2018-05-02",
