  {
    "id": "6351a9b4-3446-454f-a6c7-4dcf6d8695bb",
    "sentence": "The Committee will monitor economic and financial developments carefully and will act as needed to promote sustainable economic growth and price stability.",
    "source": "statement_20081029.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2008-10-29",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "1019be37-e45d-4ce6-9cbb-56cced156da7",
    "sentence": "Strains in global financial markets have eased, though they continue to pose significant downside risks to the economic outlook.",
    "source": "statement_20120313.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2012-03-13",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a1508718-702d-452a-8897-c01e65318a92",
    "sentence": "We all continue to work together and will take appropriate steps to address those liquidity pressures.",
    "source": "statement_20080311.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2008-03-11",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "75f309a1-dc2b-4450-ae54-643e86e30cc3",
    "sentence": "The Committee expects inflation to moderate in coming quarters, but it will be necessary to continue to monitor inflation developments carefully.",
    "source": "statement_20080130.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2008-01-30",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "dfd2ccb5-466d-4814-827e-b3c6fe5e4dec",
    "sentence": "The Committee also is prepared to purchase longer-term Treasury securities if evolving circumstances indicate that such transactions would be particularly effective in improving conditions in private credit markets.",
    "source": "statement_20090128.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2009-01-28",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "2f9a6bbf-371b-4511-b5d7-8d3f3530055e",
    "sentence": "The Committee also decided to keep the target range for the federal funds rate at 0 to 1/4 percent and currently anticipates that economic conditions--including low rates of resource utilization and a subdued outlook for inflation over the medium run--are likely to warrant exceptionally low levels for the federal funds rate at least through mid-2013.",
    "source": "statement_20111213.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2011-12-13",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "64d8cb30-4026-4d71-b63e-9ec80cba2bd9",
    "sentence": "President Plosser objected to the guidance indicating that it likely will be appropriate to maintain the current target range for the federal funds rate for \"a considerable time after the asset purchase program ends,\" because such language is time dependent and does not reflect the considerable economic progress that has been made toward the Committee's goals.",
    "source": "statement_20140917.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2014-09-17",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "fd958800-1217-4b96-bb06-01a0fde5c6fe",
    "sentence": "The Federal Reserve will consult with primary dealers on technical design features of the TSLF.",
    "source": "statement_20080311.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2008-03-11",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f2175b45-ac01-4742-8f33-66dbde89fd12",
    "sentence": "In light of ongoing improvements in the functioning of financial markets, the Committee and the Board of Governors anticipate that most of the Federal Reserveâs special liquidity facilities will expire on February 1, 2010, consistent with the Federal Reserveâs announcement of June 25, 2009.",
    "source": "statement_20091216.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2009-12-16",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "9402950b-1b50-49d6-b60b-ad32672d974f",
    "sentence": "In view of realized and expected labor market conditions and inflation, the Committee decided to raise the target range for the federal funds rate to 1/2 to 3/4 percent.",
    "source": "statement_20161214.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2016-12-14",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "1be36515-cc09-4221-8690-d2f683a91924",
    "sentence": "Plans for Reducing the Size of the Federal Reserve's Balance Sheet",
    "source": "statement_20220504.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2022-05-04",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "530fbbed-524f-4efa-9ddb-b3c66711f134",
    "sentence": "With inflation having run persistently below this longer-run goal, the Committee will aim to achieve inflation moderately above 2 percent for some time so that inflation averages 2 percent over time and longerâterm inflation expectations remain well anchored at 2 percent.",
    "source": "statement_20211103.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2021-11-03",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "50c215ea-d08c-482e-afb1-60abed2db3e5",
    "sentence": "Inflation is anticipated to remain near its recent low level in the near term, but the Committee expects inflation to rise gradually toward 2 percent over the medium term as the labor market improves further and the transitory effects of declines in energy and import prices dissipate.",
    "source": "statement_20150429.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2015-04-29",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "25d928b1-7b2c-4211-ad0f-01149ed4f8e0",
    "sentence": "The anticipated expiration dates for the Term Asset-Backed Securities Loan Facility remain set at June 30 for loans backed by new-issue commercial mortgage-backed securities and March 31 for loans backed by all other types of collateral.",
    "source": "statement_20100127.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2010-01-27",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "32e6f579-4e7c-400a-85fa-47c81a077483",
    "sentence": "In light of the substantial further progress the economy has made toward the Committee's goals since last December, the Committee decided to begin reducing the monthly pace of its net asset purchases by $10 billion for Treasury securities and $5 billion for agency mortgage-backed securities.",
    "source": "statement_20211103.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2021-11-03",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "0caa877f-c2f1-4eff-ae91-7d2fb1037f6c",
    "sentence": "However, global economic and financial developments continue to pose risks.",
    "source": "statement_20160316.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2016-03-16",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "290b39be-0161-4a67-b584-da6ec74730e9",
    "sentence": "The Committee will closely monitor incoming information on economic and financial developments and will provide additional accommodation as needed to promote a stronger economic recovery and sustained improvement in labor market conditions in a context of price stability.",
    "source": "statement_20120801.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2012-08-01",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b93cabb7-526a-4413-bc19-2a21afd07ece",
    "sentence": "President Fisher believed that the continued strengthening of the real economy, improved outlook for labor utilization and for general price stability, and continued signs of financial market excess, will likely warrant an earlier reduction in monetary accommodation than is suggested by the Committee's stated forward guidance.",
    "source": "statement_20140917.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2014-09-17",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4808a163-c4cf-4377-a92f-686efda9301e",
    "sentence": "In particular, the Committee decided to keep the target range for the federal funds rate at 0 to 1/4 percent and currently anticipates that this exceptionally low range for the federal funds rate will be appropriate at least as long as the unemployment rate remains above 6-1/2 percent, inflation between one and two years ahead is projected to be no more than a half percentage point above the Committeeâs 2 percent longer-run goal, and longer-term inflation expectations continue to be well anchored.",
    "source": "statement_20130130.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2013-01-30",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e59aec16-e6fe-4fcb-a430-07305f95a5a7",
    "sentence": "Federal Reserve Actions The Federal Open Market Committee has authorized temporary reciprocal currency arrangements (swap lines) with the Bank of Canada, the Bank of England, the European Central Bank (ECB), and the Swiss National Bank.",
    "source": "statement_20100509.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2010-05-09",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a725e38f-098b-4eaf-977f-287f7b3575af",
    "sentence": "The Committee seeks to achieve maximum employment and inflation at the rate of 2 percent over the longer run.",
    "source": "statement_20251210.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2025-12-10",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "417c2122-cdbd-4887-a2e9-1bbfdb642833",
    "sentence": "In current circumstances, depository institutions may experience unusual funding needs because of dislocations in money and credit markets.",
    "source": "statement_20070810.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2007-08-10",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "64aa6052-e8e6-4a3e-b018-c25aa99df135",
    "sentence": "Still, uncertainty about the inflation outlook has increased.",
    "source": "statement_20080318.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2008-03-18",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "1d66fbcc-c234-431a-b252-9afdc6a3d5ba",
    "sentence": "The Committee will continue to monitor the implications of incoming information for the economic outlook, including global developments and muted inflation pressures, as it assesses the appropriate path of the target range for the federal funds rate.",
    "source": "statement_20200129.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2020-01-29",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "27db794a-6c9d-47fb-8431-828ce29a9818",
    "sentence": "The Committee judges that the case for an increase in the federal funds rate has strengthened but decided, for the time being, to wait for further evidence of continued progress toward its objectives.",
    "source": "statement_20160921.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2016-09-21",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8a3feb0f-5697-4877-a78b-d2c45ee9c1f7",
    "sentence": "The Federal Reserve's ongoing purchases and holdings of securities will continue to foster smooth market functioning and accommodative financial conditions, thereby supporting the flow of credit to households and businesses.",
    "source": "statement_20220126.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2022-01-26",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "95b85a83-e87c-48b0-a403-9106e556e5eb",
    "sentence": "Inflation is expected to rise to 2 percent over the medium term as the transitory effects of declines in energy and import prices dissipate and the labor market strengthens further.",
    "source": "statement_20151216.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2015-12-16",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "09549b3e-139c-48ed-bacf-fbf854b77cee",
    "sentence": "In a related action, the Board of Governors unanimously approved a 25-basis-point decrease in the discount rate to 4-3/4 percent. In taking this action, the Board approved the requests submitted by the Boards of Directors of the Federal Reserve Banks of New York, Philadelphia, Cleveland, Richmond, Atlanta, Chicago, and St. Louis.",
    "source": "statement_20071211.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2007-12-11",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "07c8d637-64fb-4c5d-974b-edd572fea926",
    "sentence": "The Committee will closely monitor incoming information and assess the implications for monetary policy.",
    "source": "statement_20230322.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2023-03-22",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b88274b3-2669-4f4d-b5ac-aa7d8bb8b008",
    "sentence": "Mr. Hoenig also was concerned that this continued high level of monetary accommodation increased the risks of future financial imbalances and, over time, would cause an increase in long-term inflation expectations that could destabilize the economy.",
    "source": "statement_20101103.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2010-11-03",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "168c3dce-ba48-4665-95de-e738fe8d8593",
    "sentence": "For the time being, the Committee is maintaining its existing policy of reinvesting principal payments from its holdings of agency debt and agency mortgage-backed securities in agency mortgage-backed securities and of rolling over maturing Treasury securities at auction.",
    "source": "statement_20170726.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2017-07-26",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c3f3854e-fd2e-493b-9319-bc64a793ddae",
    "sentence": "The Federal Reserve is providing liquidity to facilitate the orderly functioning of financial markets.",
    "source": "statement_20070810.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2007-08-10",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "2d403a93-08f5-424d-9d77-3db7a104465c",
    "sentence": "Todayâs policy action, combined with those taken earlier, should help to promote moderate growth over time and to mitigate the risks to economic activity.",
    "source": "statement_20080130.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2008-01-30",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "7bb7b930-391c-4b37-b676-666a129572a4",
    "sentence": "The Committee is maintaining its existing policy of reinvesting principal payments from its holdings of agency debt and agency mortgage-backed securities in agency mortgage-backed securities.",
    "source": "statement_20120620.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2012-06-20",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f0755b8e-11c6-4b90-8b10-5e28b72a70e0",
    "sentence": "In a related action, the Board of Governors unanimously approved a 50-basis-point decrease in the discount rate to 1-1/4 percent. In taking this action, the Board approved the requests submitted by the Boards of Directors of the Federal Reserve Banks of Boston, New York, Cleveland, and San Francisco.",
    "source": "statement_20081029.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2008-10-29",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "18ae8d5a-4d31-430a-bceb-f7ca8d332c4c",
    "sentence": "The Committee recognizes that inflation persistently below its 2 percent objective could pose risks to economic performance, and it is monitoring inflation developments carefully for evidence that inflation will move back toward its objective over the medium term.",
    "source": "statement_20140618.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2014-06-18",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6d74f3b7-a3c8-4bf1-a2cc-8a7ede36a126",
    "sentence": "In determining how long to maintain a highly accommodative stance of monetary policy, the Committee will also consider other information, including additional measures of labor market conditions, indicators of inflation pressures and inflation expectations, and readings on financial developments. The Committee now anticipates, based on its assessment of these factors, that it likely will be appropriate to maintain the current target range for the federal funds rate well past the time that the unemployment rate declines below 6-1/2 percent, especially if projected inflation continues to run below the Committee's 2 percent longer-run goal.",
    "source": "statement_20131218.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2013-12-18",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "54a28c3f-32f1-4836-a43a-d5328ae4dcb0",
    "sentence": "Hurricane-related disruptions and rebuilding have affected economic activity, employment, and inflation in recent months but have not materially altered the outlook for the national economy. Consequently, the Committee continues to expect that, with gradual adjustments in the stance of monetary policy, economic activity will expand at a moderate pace and labor market conditions will remain strong.",
    "source": "statement_20171213.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2017-12-13",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f80974e5-8453-4073-8df9-39651336a5e7",
    "sentence": "Moreover, the Committee sees some risk that inflation could persist for a time below rates that best foster economic growth and price stability in the longer term.",
    "source": "statement_20090128.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2009-01-28",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d6dd852e-9895-4bbe-8451-de296579675f",
    "sentence": "Financial conditions have become less supportive of economic growth on balance, largely reflecting developments abroad.",
    "source": "statement_20100623.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2010-06-23",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "dc6b18e4-8290-4e93-8d78-d6f8238424c8",
    "sentence": "The stance of monetary policy remains accommodative after this increase, thereby supporting further improvement in labor market conditions and a return to 2 percent inflation.",
    "source": "statement_20151216.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2015-12-16",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "653cd6da-20e9-497c-9896-ca231da02f91",
    "sentence": "In light of the cumulative progress toward maximum employment and the improvement in the outlook for labor market conditions, the Committee decided to modestly reduce the pace of its asset purchases.",
    "source": "statement_20131218.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2013-12-18",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "34b9e975-edf2-4134-8e35-471a6c35e873",
    "sentence": "As is the case with the current securities lending program, securities will be made available through an auction process.",
    "source": "statement_20080311.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2008-03-11",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4464156f-93e7-4533-8eb4-0bee065bccca",
    "sentence": "The Committee currently expects that, with gradual adjustments in the stance of monetary policy, economic activity will expand at a moderate pace and labor market indicators will continue to strengthen.",
    "source": "statement_20160316.txt",
    "doc_type": "statement",
    "date": "2016-03-16",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
